      <section id="id14690203">
        <title>Activity: To determine the meaning of the term “soluble” [LO 2.3]</title>
        <para id="id21694695">A drop of water consists of thousands of small water particles. Sugar also consists of small particles. When sugar is added to water the grains of sugar break down into smaller pieces. These small sugar particles fit between the particles of water. We call this mixture a solution.</para>
        <para id="id13819837">
          <figure id="id21555369">
